ta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":19,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705189,"age":54,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When John de Peverell I was born in 1205, in Wimborne, Dorset, England, United Kingdom, his father, William de Peverell III, was 33 and his mother, Agnes de Mainsbridge, was 33. He married Henrietta Snook in Bere Regis, Dorset, England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died in 1273, in Bradford Peverell, Dorset, England, at the age of 68."},"et":{"1205–1273":"1205–1273","1190–1237":"1190–1237","1198–1223":"1198–1223","1210–Female":"1210–Surnud","1233–1305":"1233–1305","1235–1273":"1235–1273","1172–Male":"1172–Surnud","1172–1244":"1172–1244","1190":"1190","about 1190":"umbes 1190","1198":"1198","1273":"1273","1172":"1172","1305":"1305","1205":"1205","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1237":"1237","1235":"1235","1224":"1224","1223":"1223","1233":"1233","1244":"1244","1210":"1210","Bradford Peverell, Dorset, England":"Bradford Peverell, Dorset, England","Devonshire, England":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England","Newton-Peverell, Wimbor